document.full_text: sienna miller accepted 100,000 pounds ($162,500) damages and an unconditional admission of liability from a newspaper that snooped on her phone messages, a scandal that embarrassed rupert murdoch's news corp while it seeks approval for a huge merger.
document.title: miller accepts payout in news corp phone snoop case
